    "objectID": "Day 12 Practical.html#question-3",
    "href": "Day 12 Practical.html#question-3",
    "title": "Prac day 12",
    "section": "Question 3",
    "text": "Question 3\nEstimate coverage of a percentile bootstrap confidence interval for the following scenario: sample of size 50 from an exponential distribution with mean 1.\n\nAnswer\nThe true mean estimate has been given which is 1\n\nmean_estimate &lt;- 1\n\nCoverage after bootstrapping\n\nset.seed(123)\nc2 &lt;- makeCluster(5) # assigned 5 workers \nregisterDoParallel(c2)\n# calculated coverage for each 1000 boostraps\ncoverage &lt;- foreach(i = 1:1000, .combine = \"rbind\") %dopar%{\n  values = rexp(50,1)\n  cases = replicate(1000, mean(sample(values, size = 50 , replace = T)))\n  p_CI = quantile(cases, probs = c(0.025, 0.975))\n  c(1 &gt;= p_CI[1] && 1 &lt;= p_CI[2])\n}\n\nstopCluster(c2)\n\nmean(coverage)\n\n[1] 0.931",
    "crumbs": [
      "<span class='chapter-number'>2</span>  <span class='chapter-title'>Prac day 12</span>"
    ]
  },
  {
    "objectID": "Day 12 Practical.html#question-4",
    "href": "Day 12 Practical.html#question-4",
    "title": "Prac day 12",
    "section": "Question 4",
    "text": "Question 4\nThe package iterators provides several functions that can be used to create sequences for the foreach function. For example, the irnorm function creates an object that iterates over vectors of normally distributed random numbers. It is useful when you need to use random variables drawn from one distribution in an expression that is run in parallel.\nIn this exercise, use the foreach and irnorm functions to iterate over 3 vectors, each containing 5 random variables. Find the largest value in each vector, and print those largest values.\nBefore running the foreach function set the seed to 1234.\n\nAnswer\n\nset.seed(1234)\n# creates 3 vectors with 5 vales from a normal distribution and then \nLarge &lt;- foreach(i = 1:3, .combine = 'rbind') %do% {\n  vec = irnorm(n =5, count = 3)\n  value = foreach(x = vec, .combine = c) %do% {\n    x                                           # extracts each value x in each iteration\n  }\n  largest = max(value)\n  c(round(largest, 2))             # Extracts the largest value from each iteration \n}\n\n#changed row and column names\ncolnames(Large) &lt;- c(\"Largest Value\")\nrownames(Large) &lt;- c(\"Vector 1\", \"Vector 2\", \"Vector 3\")\n\n#produces a table with the output\nLarge %&gt;% \n  kable(caption = \"Table 2: Largest values of 3 vectors with normally distributed values\") %&gt;% \n  kable_styling(bootstrap_options = \"striped\", \"hover\", full_width = T)\n\n\nTable 2: Largest values of 3 vectors with normally distributed values\n\n\n\nLargest Value\n\n\n\n\nVector 1\n1.08\n\n\nVector 2\n2.42\n\n\nVector 3\n1.45",
    "crumbs": [
      "<span class='chapter-number'>2</span>  <span class='chapter-title'>Prac day 12</span>"
    ]
  },
  {
    "objectID": "Day 12 Practical.html#question-5",
    "href": "Day 12 Practical.html#question-5",
    "title": "Prac day 12",
    "section": "Question 5",
    "text": "Question 5\nCompare run time between parLapply, foreach and replicate for the above problem.\nUsing foreach\n\nset.seed(1234)\n#stores the time it takes to to Q4 using foreach\ntime1&lt;- system.time({\n  foreach(i = 1:3, .combine = c) %do% {\n    vec = irnorm(n =5, count = 3)\n    value = foreach(x = vec, .combine = c) %do% {\n      x\n    }\n    largest = max(value)\n    c(largest)\n}})\n\nusing replicate\n\nset.seed(1234)\n#stores the time it takes to use replicate method for Q4\ntime2 &lt;- system.time({\nlargest = replicate(3, max(rnorm(5)))\n})\n\nusing parLappy\n\n# stores the time it takes to use the parLapply function for Q4\nset.seed(1234)\ntime3 &lt;- system.time({\nc3 &lt;- makeCluster(2)\nrnorm_max &lt;- function(i){\n  values = rnorm(5)\n  return(max(values))\n}\n\nlargest &lt;- parLapply(c3, as.list(1:3), rnorm_max)\n\nstopCluster(c3)\n})\n\nTable to compare times\n\ntimes &lt;- rbind(time1, time2, time3)\ntimes &lt;- times [,-c(4,5)]\n# changes column and rownames\ncolnames(times) &lt;- c(\"user\", \"system\", \"elapsed\")\nrownames(times)&lt;- c(\"foreach\", \"replicate\", \"parLapply\")\n\ntimes %&gt;% \n  kable(caption = \"Table 3: Time usage for each method\") %&gt;% \n  kable_styling(bootstrap_options = \"striped\", \"hover\") \n\n\nTable 3: Time usage for each method\n\n\n\nuser\nsystem\nelapsed\n\n\n\n\nforeach\n0.01\n0.02\n0.01\n\n\nreplicate\n0.00\n0.00\n0.00\n\n\nparLapply\n0.03\n0.02\n0.48\n\n\n\n\n\nFrom Table 3 , the fastest method is using replicate and the method with the longest waiting time is parLapply.",
    "crumbs": [
      "<span class='chapter-number'>2</span>  <span class='chapter-title'>Prac day 12</span>"
    ]
  }
